  lines:
  - isPlayer: 0
    line: Oh, another one. Thank thou the Lord of the Near and Nigh!
  - isPlayer: 1
    line: "Another one? Was the other one Kwolan? My height, darker skin, sharp nose\u2026"
  - isPlayer: 0
    line: I shall not speak of that vulgarian. Out of sight, out of mind.
  - isPlayer: 1
    line: Why not? Where is he? Where did he go?
  - isPlayer: 0
    line: "\u2026"
  - isPlayer: 1
    line: Could you please tell me where he is?
  - isPlayer: 0
    line: Thou art kind, unlike that profane scoundrel. I shall answer thy questions
      on one condition.
  - isPlayer: 0
    line: If thou canst help me, I will help thee.
  - isPlayer: 1
    line: Sure, what do you need?
  - isPlayer: 0
    line: Dost thou know why the caged jaguar sings?
  - isPlayer: 1
    line: Why does the caged jaguar sing?
  - isPlayer: 0
    line: "I don\u2019t know, I thought thou might."
  - isPlayer: 1
    line: The caged jaguar sings because he has a beautiful voice, he wants to show
      off.
  - isPlayer: 0
    line: Thine thoughts art unpregnant.
  - isPlayer: 1
    line: Pregnant? What? Why do you talk like that?
  - isPlayer: 0
    line: I am the Mirrored One
  - isPlayer: 1
    line: Is that supposed to ring a bell?
  - isPlayer: 0
    line: I am the embodiment of the Ocelotl, Enemy of Both Sides.
  - isPlayer: 1
    line: Ocelotl? Do you mean that jaguar person?
  - isPlayer: 0
    line: YES DUDE. That jaguar person. How can you not know a major god?
  - isPlayer: 0
    line: Ugh! You both are so frustrating. First that idiot comes and pisses my
      jaguar off and then you.
  - isPlayer: 1
    line: 'Sorry, friend! We did not grow up in a religious environment. '
  - isPlayer: 0
    line: Oh how I envy you. Look at me trying to serenade a fuckin cat. Mirrored
      One my ass!
  - isPlayer: 1
    line: Hey hey hey! Relax. What is really going on here?
  - isPlayer: 0
    line: During the festivities of Ocelotl, they cast a Mirrored One, who impersonates
      the god for a year.
  - isPlayer: 0
    line: Living as a god for a year. Everyone treats you as one. Sign me the fuck
      up, one thinks.
  - isPlayer: 0
    line: "Here is the catch though. When the next festival arrives, the Mirrored
      One must speak his word. I couldn\u2019t come up with it."
  - isPlayer: 1
    line: What do you mean by his word?
  - isPlayer: 0
    line: A cursed poem. Mirrored One recites a poem in the next festival and hands
      the role over. Guess, who does not have a poem?
  - isPlayer: 1
    line: What is its relation to the big paws over there?
  - isPlayer: 0
    line: Traditionally, one must bless the poem by reading it to a jaguar. If the
      jaguar likes it, it is considered divine approval.
  - isPlayer: 0
    line: "That bastard, Kawaran, scared the jaguar. Now it won\u2019t let me get
      close. How am I supposed to get its blessing?"
  - isPlayer: 1
    line: "Do you really need it? Can\u2019t you just fake it?"
  - isPlayer: 0
    line: "That will bring bad luck for the rest of my life. C\u2019mon, I will tell
      you where he went."
  - isPlayer: 0
    line: And, I have what you are looking for. Help me and the glyph is yours.
  - isPlayer: 1
    line: Alright! What do I do?
  - isPlayer: 0
    line: I will recite the poem and you will tell it to the jaguar.
  - isPlayer: 1
    line: Ok, hit me.
  - isPlayer: 0
    line: 'If this huge ass cat comes down the tree For certain, one will flee '
  - isPlayer: 0
    line: "It won\u2019t hesitate to put thou in a ditch This is the Mirrored One\u2019s
      perfect pitch "
  - isPlayer: 1
    line: I can already tell this is not the one.
  - isPlayer: 0
    line: You are not the judge of that. So please.
